For a few years we used to do this thing on NYE where I'd get a bunch of mates to dress up in crazy shit, put a 10 piece funk band and 80 punters in a 60 capacity venue, dress up in a purple velvet pimp suit and call myself Dr Chunkyfunk. Were giving this year a proper send off in the traditional was as old as time itself. Dr Chunkyfunk at the Basement Bar Bendigo for new years... if you want to get loud and rowdy and sweaty you need to come. 
#funk #funkrock #nye #newyearseve #bendigo

Okay so.. this is very short notice and quite different. But for a few months now I've been working on starting a super cool side project where myself, @backbeatbrown @shaunklinger and the @keeper_of_the_groove play all my and other peoples alt country/Americana songs. We will be having our first gig tonight as Bill Barber and the Holding Cell at the Yorkshire Stingo. Come watch the birth of a band!

Hi my name is Bill and I'm a... guitarist 
I do this and have done this quite a lot for quite a long time. The places to play the guitar are usually pubs, so I been in hundreds of them (up until a couple years ago thrown out of quite a few too) 
But I can quite confidently say that The Delatite in Mansfield is my favourite pub to play guitar in. Theres places I love, but not as much as this joint. I'll be there with my band on Saturday evening and I'm very exited. Come hang out with us please.
